==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌfɪn|-ʌfɪn]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{cattag|foods}} a type of [[pastry]]
# {{cattag|computing}} a mechanism used in the Java Network Launching Protocol analogous to the [[cookie]] mechanism and which permits a program running in a [[browser]] to perform operations on a client machine
# {{cattag|slang}} a term of endearment, e.g. "nuffin' muffin"
# {{cattag|slang}} a vulva
# {{cattag|baseball|slang}} an 1800s baseball term meaning a less-talented player
# {{cattag|slang}} a charming and attractive male typically under the age of 25

====Quotations====
''computer term''
*'''2001''': The name/value pairs provided by the PersistenceService are similar to browser cookies. The Java Web Start implementation honors this legacy by naming the pairs "'''muffins'''." &mdash; ''JNLP and Java Web Start'', Sun Developer Network, Technical Articles and Tips, 30 May 2001.
''vagina''
*'''1989''': I wanna be stuffin' Martha's '''muffin'''!!!, &mdash; Mojo Nixon and Skid Roper ''Stuffin' Martha's Muffin''.

